        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 7:16PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 716 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Springville, or 11 miles northwest of Camden, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Camden, Springville, Big Sandy, Manleyville, Haigler Ridge, and Old
Springville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
